## Summary
The Experiment JVM SDK is a server-side implementation for Amplitude Experiment that supports both remote and local evaluation of feature flags in Java and Kotlin applications. It provides methods for initializing clients, fetching/evaluating variants for users, and supports advanced features like cohort targeting, flag streaming, and automatic assignment tracking.

